r planets at periods shorter than 5 d and depths\ngreater than 3 millimagnitudes; however, we cannot confidently rule out\ntransits at the period of Proxima b due to incomplete orbital phase coverage\nand a lack of sensitivity to transits shallower than 4 millimagnitudes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Jan 2019 19:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 Apr 2019 18:22:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-13"}
