d\n$\\Lambda^2_{SM}/\\Lambda^2_{NP}$, directly verifiable at colliders, implies\nthat: {\\it (i)} dark matter must have a mass $\\lesssim \\Lambda_{SM}$, {\\it\n(ii)} Higgs-curvature coupling must be $\\approx 1.3\\%$, {\\it (iii)} the SM RGEs\nmust remain nearly as in the SM, and {\\it (iv)} right-handed neutrinos must\nhave a mass $\\lesssim 1000\\, {\\rm TeV}$. These signatures serve as a concise\ntestbed for symmergence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Jan 2019 10:33:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Mar 2019 11:28:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 24 Jul 2019 07:41:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-29"}
