ares do. Additionally, the energy budget in the two bands is weakly\ncorrelated. We also found comparable flare duration in optical and X-rays and\nobserved that rapidly rotating stars (e.g., with rotation period shorter than\n0.5 days) preferentially host short flares. We estimated the slope of the\ncooling path of the flares in the log(EM)-versus-log(T) plane. The values we\nobtained are affected by large uncertainties, but their nominal values suggest\nthat the flares analyzed in this paper are mainly due to single loops with no\nsustained heating occurring during the cooling phase. We also observed and\nanalyzed oscillations with a period of 500 s during one of the flares.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Jan 2019 11:18:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-27"}
