s from the\nshocked ejecta are well compatible with the predicted results from spherical\ndelayed-detonation models for Type Ia supernovae. We also find that the two\n`ears' of the remnant are dominated by Si- and S-rich ejecta, thus favoring a\npre-explosion jets scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Jan 2019 14:53:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-20"}
